The '''Advanced Transit Association''' (ATRA)<ref>{{cite book|last1=Osif|first1=Bonnie A.|title=Using the Engineering Literature|date=9 Aug 2011|publisher=CRC Press|page=160|edition=Second|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dQnJT5J9CYgC}}</ref> is a [[Non-profit organization|non-profit organisation]] whose purpose is to encourage the development and deployment of Automated Transit Networks, including [[personal rapid transit]] systems. ATRA was formed in 1976<ref>{{cite web|last1=Anderson, P. E.|first1=J. Edward|title=Some Lessons from the History of Personal Rapid Transit (PRT)|url=http://faculty.washington.edu/jbs/itrans/history.htm|website=faculty.washington.edu }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Innovation in Transportation: Proceedings of a Workshop, September 24-26, 1979, National Academy of Sciences, Washington, Part 3|date=1980|publisher=National Academies|page=189|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OzkrAAAAYAAJ}}</ref> and in 1988 published a report<ref>{{cite journal|title=Personal Rapid Transit (PRT): Another Option for Urban Transit?|journal=Journal of Advanced Transportation|date=1988|id=22:192-314}}</ref> that became an essential factor in increasing the credibility of the [[personal rapid transit]] concept.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Jones Jr.|first1=Steven L.|title=Urban Public Transportation Systems 2013|date=1 Nov 2013|publisher=ASCE Publications|page=348|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oQY4AgAAQBAJ}}</ref>
== Publications == "Advanced Transit and Urban Revitalization, an International Dialogue" was published by the ATRA at an international conference in Indianapolis in 1978.<ref>{{cite book|title=Advanced Transit Association International Conference: "Advanced Transit and Urban Revitalization, an International Dialogue" : Proceedings, Indianapolis, 1978, Volume 1|date=1978|publisher=Advanced Transit Association|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uH5FAAAAYAAJ}}</ref>
