[[File:Addpac gsm voip gateways.jpg|thumb|150px|VoIP GSM gateways Addpac with a SIM box inside]] A '''SIM box''' (also called a '''SIM bank''') is device used as part of a [[VoIP gateway]] installation. It contains a number of [[Subscriber identity module|SIM cards]], which are linked to the gateway but housed and stored separately from it. A SIM box can have SIM cards of different mobile operators installed, permitting it to operate with several [[GSM gateway]]s located in different places.{{citation-needed|date=October 2015}}
==Usage and detection== [[File:Scheme of VoIP call with Sim box.png|thumb|Scheme of VoIP call with SIM box and gateway]] The SIM box operator can route [[international call]]s through the VoIP connection and connect the call as local traffic, allowing the box's operator to bypass international rates and often undercut prices charged by local [[mobile network operator]]s.<ref name="purgefraud">{{cite web | url=http://purgefraud.com/fraudpedia/bypass_fraud.php | title=How Bypass Fraud Works | work=PurgeFraud.com | accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="VibeGhana" />
This business model of operation is very common around the world and is usually legal, as it simply uses the internet to piggyback calls to a local area and using a private exchange to route the call back to the mobile network. However, many companies, such as Verizon, provide strong lobbying forces to local governments to ban the use of SIM pools. Another reason is the lack of control of the users, i.e. Knowing who called whom? Creating a serious privacy challenge to the users, where (local) governments want to know who made certain calls to whom and from where. One such example is the country of Ghana, where government has banned the use of SIM boxes. <ref name="VibeGhana">{{cite web | url=http://vibeghana.com/2015/01/26/ghana-loses-33million-dollars-through-sim-box-fraud/ | title=Ghana loses 33million dollars through SIM BOX fraud | work=vibeghana.com | date=26 January 2015 | accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="myjoyonline">{{cite web | url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2015/January-26th/former-greeda-boss-dr-tweneboah-arrested-for-sim-box-fraud.php | title=Former GREDA boss Tweneboah arrested for SIM box fraud | work=MyJoyOnline.com | date=26 January 2015 | accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref>
==Call Quality== As the normal mobile network are sometimes using a very outdated and low quality sound codecs (such as the GSM HR and FR codecs), a SIM box may provide local quality with superior sound quality.
